(3198, 5396, 'faq_0_faq_q', 'Q: Are you insured? What happens if you break a piece of my furniture?'),
(3199, 5396, '_faq_0_faq_q', 'field_587557171b82a'),
(3200, 5396, 'faq_0_faq_a', 'A: Yes, we are insured. In the event of damage, we will repair your furniture if possible. If the damaged piece is not repairable, we will pay the depreciated value of the damaged piece.'),
(3201, 5396, '_faq_0_faq_a', 'field_587557281b82b'),
(3202, 5396, 'faq_1_faq_q', 'Q: Are your movers full-time employees with experience?'),
(3203, 5396, '_faq_1_faq_q', 'field_587557171b82a'),
(3204, 5396, 'faq_1_faq_a', 'A: Yes. Many of our movers have been with us for years and our new hire criteria include professional moving experience. We are also committed to continuous training for our employees.'),
(3205, 5396, '_faq_1_faq_a', 'field_587557281b82b'),
(3206, 5396, 'faq_2_faq_q', 'Q: How do I know you’re not one of those unscrupulous residential moving companies that you see on the news that quote one price and then charge another, or damages furniture and doesn’t fix it?'),
(3207, 5396, '_faq_2_faq_q', 'field_587557171b82a'),
(3208, 5396, 'faq_2_faq_a', 'A: Austin Moving Forward is fully licensed and insured. We also have a massive collection of great testimonials from many of our satisfied customers. To read your consumer rights and responsibilities, look up important information about our company, or research any moving company visit protectyourmove.gov'),
(3209, 5396, '_faq_2_faq_a', 'field_587557281b82b'),
(3210, 5396, 'faq_3_faq_q', 'Q: How much does it cost to move?'),
(3211, 5396, '_faq_3_faq_q', 'field_587557171b82a'),
(3212, 5396, 'faq_3_faq_a', 'A: It depends on a lot of factors, but our average move was $1,500 – $2,000 last year. See Average Moving Costs for ballpark estimates, or if you would like a more accurate estimate call us at 512-201-4777.'),
(3213, 5396, '_faq_3_faq_a', 'field_587557281b82b'),
(3214, 5396, 'faq_4_faq_q', 'Q: Do I need to pack everything or what do I need to pack to prepare for the movers?'),
(3215, 5396, '_faq_4_faq_q', 'field_587557171b82a'),
(3216, 5396, 'faq_4_faq_a', 'A: If it is smaller than a breadbox, then put it in a box. Remember, you are paying your movers by the hour, and it takes us a lot less time to dolly out boxes than to carry out miscellaneous items and find safe places on the truck for it. Our movers are trained to refuse to take certain items if not properly packed.'),
(3217, 5396, '_faq_4_faq_a', 'field_587557281b82b'),
(3218, 5396, 'faq_5_faq_q', 'Q: Where do I get moving boxes?'),
(3219, 5396, '_faq_5_faq_q', 'field_587557171b82a'),
(3220, 5396, 'faq_5_faq_a', 'A: Some people try and collect miscellaneous boxes before they move. However, we have a Buy-Back Program you can take advantage of. Using uniform sized moving boxes helps the movers load the truck quicker, and since we get paid by the hour, using good boxes can save you money.'),
(3221, 5396, '_faq_5_faq_a', 'field_587557281b82b'),
(3222, 5396, 'faq_6_faq_q', 'Q: Does Austin Moving Forward sell moving boxes?'),
(3223, 5396, '_faq_6_faq_q', 'field_587557171b82a'),
(3224, 5396, 'faq_6_faq_a', 'A: Yes. We carry a complete line of boxes and moving supplies and we offer free delivery if you are moving with us. Explore our options with the box Buy-Back Program.\r\n'),
(3225, 5396, '_faq_6_faq_a', 'field_587557281b82b'),
(3226, 5396, 'faq_7_faq_q', 'Q: Do I need to empty the clothes out of my dresser drawers?'),
(3227, 5396, '_faq_7_faq_q', 'field_587557171b82a'),
(3228, 5396, 'faq_7_faq_a', 'A: No. There is no need to use the extra boxes. Our movers can handle the extra weight. However, you will need to remove any loose items in the drawers, like papers, change or jewelry.\r\n'),
(3229, 5396, '_faq_7_faq_a', 'field_587557281b82b'),
(3230, 5396, 'faq_8_faq_q', 'Q: What do I do with the clothes in my closet?'),
(3231, 5396, '_faq_8_faq_q', 'field_587557171b82a'),
(3232, 5396, 'faq_8_faq_a', 'A: We rent a specialty box called a wardrobe box. Explore our Buy-Back Program.'),
(3233, 5396, '_faq_8_faq_a', 'field_587557281b82b'),
(3234, 5396, 'faq_9_faq_q', 'Q: What can I do to save money on my move?'),
(3235, 5396, '_faq_9_faq_q', 'field_587557171b82a'),
(3236, 5396, 'faq_9_faq_a', 'A: The biggest thing you can do to save money is to be prepared for the movers. Have everything packed up and ready to go. Stack boxes 4 high (to easily load on dolly) in the living room or garage and allow movers to put them all in one room at the unload. Disassemble beds, take mirrors off dressers, and prepare all furniture to be moved. Be available to answer the movers’ questions regarding furniture placement. Don’t plan anything else for moving day.'),
