(799, 2, '2015-03-17 14:52:12', '2015-03-17 14:52:12', '<span style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-family: jockey one,sans-serif;">Ask for a free in home estimate!</span></span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-family: jockey one,sans-serif;">If Austin Moving Forward is coming out to you it''s important to make the most of your time, and ours by being prepared. Have your home organized, and show the estimator your whole house. Know what is going with you and what isn''t going. If you aren''t sure, be honest with the estimator. You can always update them after if there are changes.</span></span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-family: jockey one,sans-serif;">Having a list of questions ready is helpful. The estimator will have questions for you, but it''s important for you to say what your expectations are regarding moving dates and if your new residence has certain requirements for moving. </span></span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-family: jockey one,sans-serif;">If you are getting more than one estimate, it''s key to give the same information to all involved so that you can make an informed decision knowing that the quotes are comparing the same services. It can be helpful to share your estimates with other companies to decipher where the differences lay. It''s important to make sure you understand the moving estimates and the services that each company is providing. </span></span>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', 'Free In Home Estimates', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'free-in-home-estimates', '', '', '2015-03-17 14:52:12', '2015-03-17 14:52:12', '', 0, 'http://amf.dev/free-in-home-estimates/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
