(808, 2, '2015-08-21 04:14:33', '2015-08-21 04:14:33', '<a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/GST-ALE-184-62.jpg"><img class=" wp-image-812 size-medium alignright" src="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/GST-ALE-184-62-300x300.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="300" /></a>\n\nMoving can, at times, be overwhelming.  Especially if you have a large amount of items being moved. The first step before moving is making a detailed list of all the items.  Keeping record of your items can help keep you organized throughout the moving process.\n\nIn addition to your list, most moving companies like Austin Moving Forward, will also provide you with a detailed inventory list of all of your goods.  They will also use a system of symbols for their inventory lists and it is important that you understand these symbols.   You may see inventory  lists with symbols such as: PBO- pack by owner, CP- carrier packing, CU- condition unknown, D- dented, SC- scratched, CH- chipped, BR- broken, or CR- cracked.\n\nTo ensure that your goods are all in their original condition and that they are all accounted for, it can be a good idea to compare your list with the inventory list that the moving company provides you.  Having both inventory lists on hand can help protect you from theft or damage but it can also help you keep record of which items you will want to store in a storage facility.\n\nInventory lists are key components to successful moves.  Understanding the moving company’s list and creating your own can be a big help in keeping things in order throughout.  Contact the best Austin moving company: Austin Moving Forward.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', 'The Importance of Taking Inventory', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-importance-of-taking-inventory', '', '', '2015-08-21 04:14:33', '2015-08-21 04:14:33', '', 0, 'http://www.austinmovingforward.com/?p=808', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(819, 2, '2015-08-28 15:43:51', '2015-08-28 15:43:51', '<a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Dollarphotoclub_69715614.jpg"><img class=" wp-image-820 size-medium alignright" src="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Dollarphotoclub_69715614-300x200.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="200" /></a>\n\nMoving is an exciting time when you''re packing up and starting a new chapter in a new home. It can be a tricky process, however, if not done correctly. Avoid these 4 major moving mistakes to ensure your move is hassle-free!\n<ol>\n	<li><strong>D-I-Y Moving</strong></li>\n</ol>\nMoving is always an extensive process from deciding what to take and give away to packing and loading up. Moving just across town can be complicated. There can be unexpected fuel costs, damage to your goods, and even physical stress on you. Make sure you know the extent of what’s involved before deciding to move on your own, DIY style.\n<ol start="2">\n	<li><strong>Not Getting an Estimate</strong></li>\n</ol>\nYou wouldn’t buy your new home without knowing how much it costs so it is best to treat the moving process the same way. It is wise to get estimates from various moving companies and then to choose the best quote. Austin Moving Forward makes it easy to get a quick quote here: http://www.austinmovingforward.com/get-a-quote/\n<ol start="3">\n	<li><strong>Not Cleaning House First</strong></li>\n</ol>\nOver time, things accumulate and it is hard to realize exactly how many things you actually have until you need to pack them all. Instead of having to pack and move all the things that you haven’t used in years, sort through things that you need to take and the things you can give away or sell. This way, you’re left with less clutter and less things to pack, move and unpack.\n<ol start="4">\n	<li><strong>Not Checking and Double Checking the Inventory List</strong></li>\n</ol>\nIn our previous <a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/the-importance-of-taking-inventory/">blog</a>, we stated the importance of having an inventory list of your own and from the moving company. Check the inventory list before everything is packed and ready to go and also check the list when you arrive at your new residence to ensure nothing was left behind or forgotten.\n\n&nbsp;', '4 Major Moving Mistakes', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '4-major-moving-mistakes', '', '', '2015-08-28 15:43:51', '2015-08-28 15:43:51', '', 0, 'http://www.austinmovingforward.com/?p=819', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(825, 2, '2015-09-10 15:44:00', '2015-09-10 15:44:00', '<a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/eco7.jpg"><img class="alignright wp-image-826 " src="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/eco7-300x300.jpg" alt="eco7" width="268" height="268" /></a>As we learn more and more about how our daily lives affect the environment, we are learning that is important to be environmentally conscious as much as possible. “Going green” is taking steps to help reduce carbon footprint and be more eco-friendly. Why not make your move green too? Try these tips to stay eco-friendly during the moving process.\n\n<span style="color: #258a43;"><strong>Donate Items</strong></span>\n\nYou never really know how many items you have accumulated until you start to pack it all and move it. Starting the packing process may help you sort through items that you don’t want to take with you. Instead of taking these unwanted items to the garbage, you might consider donating them. This not only reduces the number of items you have to pack and move,\nit also allows items to be reused by others instead of ending up in a landfill.\n\n<span style="color: #258a43;"><strong>Participate in a Buy Back Program</strong></span>\n\nAustin Moving Forward strives to be as eco-friendly as possible so we offer a friendly service called our <a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/buy-back-program/">Box Buy Back Program</a>. How does it work? You leave a <a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/buy-back-program/">partially refundable deposit</a> for the cost of the boxes. You’re able to keep as many boxes as you’d like but the ones you return will continue to be reused until they’re no longer in a useable condition. After that, we recycle the boxes, making moving a little greener, one reusable box at a time.\n\n<span style="color: #258a43;"><strong>Use “Green” Cleaning Products</strong></span>\n\nCleaning is also a large part of the moving process. Whether you’re shining up your new home or scrubbing down your old one, using eco-friendly products is easy and helpful in preserving our precious environment. Try using all natural products or look for an environmentally conscious brand that provides green cleaning products.\n\nIf a greener move is your mission, try following these simple tips to stay green and keep the environment in mind throughout the moving process.', '3 Ways to Make Your Move More Green', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '3-ways-to-make-your-move-more-green', '', '', '2015-09-10 15:44:00', '2015-09-10 15:44:00', '', 0, 'http://www.austinmovingforward.com/?p=825', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(831, 2, '2015-09-18 16:34:35', '2015-09-18 16:34:35', '<a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Untitled-design-4.jpg"><img class=" size-full wp-image-832 alignright" src="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Untitled-design-4.jpg" alt="Untitled design (4)" width="300" height="300" /></a>Are you planning a move to one of the fastest growing cities in the country? Or maybe you’re one of the 10,000 people already living in downtown Austin but are looking to upgrade to a newer condo. Either way, downtown Austin is a beloved area that offers a wide range of activities for everyone to enjoy. Downtown is the center of it all with hike and bike trails, vibrant business and artistic communities, and a variety of condo living spaces.\n\nAs Austin continues to grow and the influx of people increases, condos in the downtown ATX area are quickly becoming prime real estate. There is a unique mix of old and traditional condos and homes and new, modern homes and apartments. As of now, there are around 5,000 condos being built downtown and about 5,600 apartment units for rent. These options come in all different sizes and price ranges and many have unparalleled views overlooking the city and the lake. Many of these condos are also at a close proximity to shops, restaurants, and the great outdoors.\n\nLiving downtown means you are the very core of this vivacious city we call Austin in which there is never a shortage of activities to enjoy. One thing that appeals to many residents and future residents is Lady Bird Lake (formerly known as Town Lake). Along the lake there are several places that offer paddle boats, canoes, and even stand up paddle boards. In addition to the activities on the lake, there are 10 miles of hike and bike trails surrounding Lady Bird Lake that offer tranquil views and a place to exercise and break away from the busy city lifestyle.\n\nNot only does downtown offer activities for those of all ages, it also has an abundance of restaurants to enjoy. Whether you are in the mood for some classic Texas BBQ or you want to support the local economy by eating a local eatery with a farm-to-table menu, downtown Austin can satisfy all of your needs. Check out local online listings to see the full assortment of restaurants downtown has to offer.\n\nIf you are planning a move to downtown ATX, Austin Moving Forward can help you every step of the way. Get started today by requesting a free quote from us and take the first step to enjoying your new adventure in the dynamic downtown Austin, TX.', 'Moving to Downtown Austin', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'downtown-austin-living', '', '', '2015-09-18 16:34:35', '2015-09-18 16:34:35', '', 0, 'http://www.austinmovingforward.com/?p=831', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(853, 2, '2015-09-22 21:12:25', '2015-09-22 21:12:25', '<a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/null-1.jpg"><img class=" size-full wp-image-854 aligncenter" src="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/null-1.jpg" alt="null (1)" width="300" height="300" /></a>\n\nSo you’ve found your dream home and you’re ready to take that first step into packing, organizing, and preparing for that highly anticipated moment: Moving Day. The idea of getting your current home organized and ready to be moved may be daunting but fortunately, there are apps that can help you with this process. Having the assistance of mobile apps can make sure your moving day goes as well as you had imagined it would.\n<ol>\n	<li><span style="color: #258a43;"><strong>Moving Day</strong></span></li>\n</ol>\nThis free iPhone app has the ability to create and scan bar codes. In addition, Moving Day as label-making capabilities. You can create a bar code using the app, print it out, and stick the bar code to your boxes, reminding you what items are in each box without even having to open up the box.\n<ol start="2">\n	<li><span style="color: #258a43;"><strong>Move Match</strong></span></li>\n</ol>\nThis app is free but currently is only available on Android devices. Move Match can help you determine about how much your items weigh. It also allows you to create a list of all the boxes to send to your moving company explaining which box goes where.\n<ol start="3">\n	<li><span style="color: #258a43;"><strong>Moving Van</strong></span></li>\n</ol>\nA $1.99 app available solely for iPhones, Moving Van allows you to record the exact contents of each moving box. It also allows you to run a search using the app to find out which box a particular item is located in. You can even print out a comprehensive inventory list so that you have a tangible copy to check on your moving day.\n<ol start="4">\n	<li><span style="color: #258a43;"><strong>Move Planner</strong></span></li>\n</ol>\nThis $2.99 iPhone app contains 100 pre-set moving tasks that are commonly used. This app can make sure you have all of your bases covered when it comes to the moving process. You can check off tasks as they are completed. Move Planner is, essentially, a moving to-do checklist.\n\nWith the ease and convenience of mobile apps, the packing and moving processes can be made easier. Try these apps to help you prepare for your big day. For other packing and moving services that can’t be done via mobile device, contact Austin Moving Forward to find out more about the services we offer.', '4 Apps to Get You Ready for Your Move', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '4-apps-to-get-you-ready-for-your-move', '', '', '2015-09-22 21:12:25', '2015-09-22 21:12:25', '', 0, 'http://www.austinmovingforward.com/?p=853', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(870, 2, '2015-10-02 16:02:14', '2015-10-02 16:02:14', '<a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Dollarphotoclub_60262498.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-871 size-medium" src="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Dollarphotoclub_60262498-300x192.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="192" /></a>\n\nMoving is always a big life change, especially for young children. Having to pack up your entire lives and start a new one in a new home is an exciting time but can also be a bit of a shock for younger kids. Below are a couple of examples of how you can make the big move a positive experience for the kiddos.\n\nStay positive! In times of difficulty and stress, it is imperative to maintain positivity especially in front of children. Ensure them that the move is going to go well and help guide them through the process step by step. Positivity can go a long way with children especially in a transition period that is unfamiliar to them.\n\nKids may not initially understand what is going on or what their new home is going to be like. This is why it is crucial to explain to them what is happening and what they should expect from the new transition. To give put a fun twist on the moving process for kiddos, try turning the process in the game for them. For example, “I Spy” or a Scavenger Hunt can be good ways to keep kids entertained during the packing process. Help making the moving process less stressful and more enjoyable and kid-friendly.\n\nAnother way to ease the transition for young kids is to take them to their new neighborhood before moving to have them get a feel of their new life. If possible, you can show them the fun things to do around the area and maybe even meet some of the neighborhood kids. This allows the child to get familiarized with where they will be moving so that moving day is not such a culture shock.\n\nEnsure that the moving process goes smoothly by making it fun for the whole family. Austin Moving Forward can help your move be a seamless transition with a variety of packing, moving, and storage services. We do our best to be the premier Austin moving company.', 'Tips for Moving With Kids', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'tips-for-moving-with-kids', '', '', '2015-10-02 16:02:14', '2015-10-02 16:02:14', '', 0, 'http://www.austinmovingforward.com/?p=870', 0, 'post', '', 0);
