(920, 2, '2015-11-06 22:19:50', '2015-11-06 22:19:50', '<a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Dollarphotoclub_90143899.jpg"><img class="wp-image-921 size-medium alignright" src="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Dollarphotoclub_90143899-300x200.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="200" /></a>\n\nMoving day is quickly approaching and you want to be fully prepped and ready to go, right? With residential moving it''s essential to have everything in order before the actual move so the process happens seamlessly.\n\nSo, as you''re counting down the days until THE day,  think of these helpful moving tips as the move before the move.\n\n<b>Make a list.\n</b>\nWrite everything down! You’ll thank yourself later. Before you pack even one box, create a simple record keeping system. Create a computer-printed list of numbers with a space to write the contents. Or have a spiral-bound notebook for the job. You’ll place a number on EVERY box you pack and list the contents on your list. Don’t put the list down unless it’s in a place you’ll call <i>Packing Central.</i> This is where you’ll find your labels, marking pens, box tape, and other supplies. When describing the box contents, be specific — “A-D files” is better than “files”, and “Tulip dishes” rather than “misc. kitchen”. This will help you direct the movers where to place each box when moving day comes.\n\n<b>Pack ahead.\n</b>\nAnything you can pack ahead will save you time on moving day. You don’t really need 5 radios or TV’s around your house for the last few days there. Box up your shampoo and extra toothpaste and live out of a travel cosmetic case for the last week or two. Pare down cooking utensils and food supplies to bare essentials. Wastebaskets can also be packed (put things in them!) while you switch to using plastic grocery bags (hang them on a cabinet door or door handle to collect trash.)\n\n<b>Consolidate cleaning supplies.\n</b>\nIf you must clean your old place after moving out, put together a kit of basic cleaning supplies and rags. Clean anything possible ahead of time (the inside of kitchen cupboards, the oven, windows, etc.), and if possible, vacuum each room as movers empty it.\n\n<strong>Set up utilities and other services in new home.</strong>\n\nAn important step that you want to have complete before you arrive in your new home. Setting up or transferring all of your utility services, including electricity, water, and TV/Internet/Phone, at your new location is crucial. Having this done beforehand will help you get set up quickly and resume your normal life as soon as possible.\n\nLet us be a part of your residential moving process! Check out our <a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/residential-movers/" target="_blank">residential moving services</a> to see all that we provide. We also offer <a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/request-a-quote/" target="_blank">free quotes </a>here at Austin Moving Forward, your premier, local moving company.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', 'The Move Before the Move', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-move-before-the-move', '', '', '2015-11-06 22:19:50', '2015-11-06 22:19:50', '', 0, 'http://www.austinmovingforward.com/?p=920', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1021, 2, '2015-12-01 16:41:26', '2015-12-01 16:41:26', '<a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Dollarphotoclub_90075688.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1022 size-medium" src="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Dollarphotoclub_90075688-300x208.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="208" /></a>\n\nPacking your home office does not need to be stressful or tricky.  Just like preparing your home for a move, you can easily prepare your home office for a move.  Here are some simple steps for a smooth move so the electronic nerve center of your home is up and running quickly.\n\n<strong>Evaluate</strong>\n\nIs your home office pristinely clean of all papers and mail?  Or do you have a few stacks, sticky notes, old files in your file cabinet, and more?  Regardless of whether your home office is perfectly filed or the family dumping ground for all papers and more, <em>evaluate</em> what needs to be kept or thrown out.  If you have sensitive documents that can be thrown, be sure to have them professionally shredded.\n\n<strong>Important Documents</strong>\n\nWe all have important documents such as birth certificates and passports.  But other documents include specific legal documents, investment/loan/insurance information.  These are examples of documents you might want to keep with you outside of what the movers pack for you.  Place important documents in an envelope in the box of things marked specifically for you to transport.  The best option is to place that box in the car prior to the moving company arriving so the box will not get mixed up with any other boxes they are transporting.\n\n<strong>Packing</strong>\n\nIf it is not part of the home office, move it to the correct location - your new home office will be organized already.  Prior to the movers arriving, you might want to place small office supplies into zip-lock baggies (pencils, pens, paper clips, and binder clips) so they stay together.  Whether it stays in the drawers or is packed into boxes, it will be reasonably organized if it is already bagged.\n\n<strong>Electronics</strong>\n\nFirst, back up important computer files then decide if those will be kept with you or packed by the movers.  Remove toner and ink cartridges from printers.  If you have the original boxes your electronics came in, electronics can be repacked in those boxes and the movers will take care of the rest.  If you do not have the original boxes, use a color-coded system.  Use matching colored stickers to mark the port and cable so set up in your new home office is <em><u>fast</u></em>.  A label maker can be used to mark each cable.  Repurpose empty paper towel or toilet paper rolls to hold loosely wound cables, and mark the rolls with the component it goes with (printer, monitor, computer etc.).\n\nIf you''re planning a home office move and need moving services, <a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/contact-us-107/" target="_blank">contact </a>the best moving company in Austin for details.\n\nSources:\n\n<a href="http://www.pcmag.com/slideshow/story/302229/get-organized-clean-up-your-wires-cables-and-cords/">Get Organized: Clean Up Your Wires, Cables, and Cords</a>', 'Essentials for Moving the Home Office', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'essentials-for-moving-the-home-office', '', '', '2015-12-01 16:41:26', '2015-12-01 16:41:26', '', 0, 'http://www.austinmovingforward.com/?p=1021', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1024, 2, '2015-12-09 17:24:31', '2015-12-09 17:24:31', '<a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Dollarphotoclub_93274775.jpg"><img class="alignright wp-image-1026 size-medium" src="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Dollarphotoclub_93274775-300x205.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="205" /></a>\n\nA house during a move can sometimes be a disaster zone. Each room is an obstacle course of boxes (in various stages of packing), and debris of leftover tape, packing paper, and bubble wrap litters the floor. No matter how much you clean, things only seem to get worse before they get better. Between the emotional and mental stress of coordinating such a large — and important — job and the physical stress of lifting heavy furniture, moving is an incredibly uncomfortable task. But the negative impact isn’t just on your peace of mind and energy level. In the clean-up, you’re hauling bags of garbage out to the curb and spraying chemical cleaning solution over every surface imaginable. As a result, moving has a high environmental impact as well.\n\nResidential moves should be a less toxic act, both environmentally and emotionally. You should be able to move into your new home free of stress and without contributing to our society’s waste and chemical problems. At Austin Moving Forward, our goal is to help you do both of these. You should hire a local moving company (like us) for your residential move because of our reputability, our care for the community, and our commitment to environmental sustainability.\n\n<strong>A Job Well Done</strong>\n\nWe’re a local moving company, and we make your life easier by handling all the logistics of moving. Our residential movers are fully insured against damages and professionally licensed and trained, so you can rest assured the move will be done with care and intentionality. From the planning stage to the actual moving, and even the packing, our movers are accustomed to doing all the heavy lifting (figurative and literal), and aim to make your life less stressful.\n\n<strong>Care for the Community</strong>\n\nAustin is a beautiful city, and we strive to take care of the Austin community in everything we do. As local movers, we know the Austin area well, and we care about it too. We’ll treat you as a neighbor because that’s what you are to us. We care for the people of Austin by making sure every move we do is as easy as possible for the client. We care for the city of Austin by committing ourselves to environmental sustainability.\n\n<strong>Green Moving</strong>\n\nAt Austin Moving Forward, we use recycled material in our boxes, wrapping paper, and plastic. All of our adhesives are biodegradable, and our box buy-back program prevents further waste by re-using boxes (and saves you money in the process!). We hope to set an example and preserve the city we live in.\n\nIf you’re moving and need a local moving company, give us a call or<a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/get-a-quote/" target="_blank"> get a free quote!</a>', 'Benefits of Choosing a Local Moving Company for Residential Moves', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'benefits-of-choosing-a-local-moving-company-for-residential-moves', '', '', '2015-12-09 17:24:31', '2015-12-09 17:24:31', '', 0, 'http://www.austinmovingforward.com/?p=1024', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1196, 2, '2015-12-18 19:41:44', '2015-12-18 19:41:44', '<a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Dollarphotoclub_6341171.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1197 size-medium" src="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Dollarphotoclub_6341171-199x300.jpg" alt="" width="199" height="300" /></a>\n\nThe holiday season is a prime time for gifts, specifically electronics. From iPads, desktop computers, laptops and notebooks, gaming consoles, or TVs – electronics are some of the most prominent gifts in many modern day households.\n\nIf you’re planning to move in the upcoming year, it’s important to pack these electronics safely to ensure they function properly when you arrive at your new destination.\n\nHere are a few tips to keep in mind when packing up your electronics for a move:\n\n<strong>Keep electronics in their original boxes</strong>\n\nThis is one of the safest ways to ensure the protection of your expensive electronics. If you have the original container that your electronic device came in, it’s best to move and store it in that. This way, your device fits perfectly with all its accessories included.\n\n<strong>Pack electronics in full boxes with antistatic materials</strong>\n\nIf you no longer have the original box, the next best option is to pack your electronics in a box with antistatic materials inside. This means, opting out of packing peanuts and opting in for materials such as bubble wrap that won’t bring static electricity. Pack each box full so that there are no empty spaces for the electronics to shift around.\n\nPacking and moving electronics can be a tricky escapade but for residential moves, choosing the right residential moving company can make this experience easier on you and your family. Looking to move to or from Austin? You’ve come to the right place. Austin Moving Forward is your premier Austin moving company. Let us help you pack and move your electronics for a hassle-free moving experience.<a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/contact-us-107/" target="_blank"> Contact us today!</a>', 'Tips for Packing Electronics', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'tips-for-packing-electronics', '', '', '2015-12-18 19:41:44', '2015-12-18 19:41:44', '', 0, 'http://www.austinmovingforward.com/?p=1196', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1203, 2, '2016-01-05 22:13:38', '2016-01-05 22:13:38', '<a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Dollarphotoclub_50658041.jpg"><img class="alignright wp-image-1204 size-medium" src="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Dollarphotoclub_50658041-274x300.jpg" alt="" width="274" height="300" /></a>\n\nAnytime a small business moves, a smooth, seamless transition is paramount to business operations. Businesses need to get up and running as quickly as possible and that starts with getting your ducks in a row, so to speak, before the move even begins.\n\nHere are 4 things you should do to help you relocate your small business office quickly and efficiently:\n\n<strong>Create a move timeline </strong>\n\nIf you have already found your new location for your small business, creating a timeline for your commercial move is the next immediate step. It’s important to make a plan for when each element of the moving process should be completed. For example, set a deadline for when you will need to have your internet/phone services, insurance policies, and permits updated by. In your timeline, you will also want to coordinate and schedule time for packing to ensure everything is ready to go on the big day.\n\n<strong>Update your vendors</strong>\n\nKeeping your office operations running smoothly during and after the move is vital. You won’t want any important office necessities missing once you are moved to your new office, so update your vendors ahead of time of your new billing and shipping address. It’s best to do this about 1-3 months prior to the relocation.\n\n<strong>Hire movers</strong>\n\nSuccessful commercial moves and business office moves require a trusted mover. You want professional service to make a smooth transition that keeps your business moving forward. Every business depends on its customers, financial data, and even trade secrets to be successful. We recommend working with a moving team that can manage all the details and all the logistics of your commercial move. Businesses need to get up and running as quickly as possible and that starts with a reliable moving quote based on your needs. Request quotes from a variety of moving companies and choose the one that best suits you and your small business.\n\n<strong>Update your website and other marketing materials</strong>\n\nAbout 1-2 weeks before your move, update your website, letterheads, and business cards with your new information. This may include any name changes, physical address changes, and phone number changes. This is imperative to keep past, current, and future clients aware of how to contact you.\n\nPlanning ahead is essential in small business moves and makes the end process significantly easier. If you’re a small business that is planning on relocating to or from Austin, TX, contact Austin Moving Forward. We can ensure your commercial move transition is smooth and seamless.', '4 Things to Do Before Your Small Business Commercial Move', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '4-things-to-do-before-your-small-business-commercial-move', '', '', '2016-01-05 22:13:38', '2016-01-05 22:13:38', '', 0, 'http://www.austinmovingforward.com/?p=1203', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1208, 2, '2016-01-22 17:10:41', '2016-01-22 17:10:41', '<a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Dollarphotoclub_41522064.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1209 size-medium" title="residential moves" src="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Dollarphotoclub_41522064-300x200.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="200" /></a>\n\nMoving into a new home can be exciting and stressful for the whole family. Residential moves require your time, your effort, and of course, your money. Budgetary limits can be worked within if the proper planning takes place before the move. If you’re on a tight budget, here are some of the ways you can work within your budget and save money on residential moves.\n\n<strong>Get quotes from different movers</strong>\n\nDo your homework and search around for moving companies, both local movers and nationwide. Once you narrow down your list to a select few, ask for a written estimate from each. This estimate should be based on an actual inspection of the stuff you want to move. If a business isn’t willing to send a person to your home to do an estimate, cross them off the list! Movers that only offer to give quotes over the phone can often underestimate the total and may try to charge you for the difference. Moving quotes depend on a wide variety of factors, but Austin Moving Forward’s average move was $1,500 – $2,000 last year.\n\n<strong>Avoid hidden fees</strong>\n\nMake sure the movers are aware of everything that needs to be moved to avoid any added charges. The cost of your moving fee may increase if any big furniture gets added at the last-minute, so make sure the movers have an itemized list before they show up. Also, if the moving truck has trouble finding parking by your place, they can charge for the extra distance, so plan ahead!\n\n<strong>Only take what you need</strong>\n\nYou never really know how much you have accumulated until you have to pack it all. To avoid unnecessary packing and extra pennies spent on boxes, donate or throw away the things that you don’t need or want. If your current residence allows for garage sales, you could sell your unwanted items to add a bit of extra cash to your moving budget.\n\n<strong>Be prepared for the movers on moving day</strong>\n\nHave everything packed up and ready to go. Stack boxes 4 high (to easily load on dolly) in the living room or garage and allow movers to put them all in one room at the unload. Disassemble beds, take mirrors off of dressers, and basically prepare all furniture to be moved. Be available to answer the movers’ questions regarding furniture placement. Don’t plan anything else for moving day.\n\nIf you’re looking for local movers in Austin, contact Austin’s premier moving company: Austin Moving Forward. We can provide you with a <a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/get-a-quote/" target="_blank">free quote</a>, skilled moving professionals, and assistance with your residential moves.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', 'Residential Moving on a Budget', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'residential-moving-on-a-budget', '', '', '2016-01-22 17:10:41', '2016-01-22 17:10:41', '', 0, 'http://www.austinmovingforward.com/?p=1208', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1211, 2, '2016-01-28 18:30:17', '2016-01-28 18:30:17', '<a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Dollarphotoclub_99359996resized.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-1213 size-medium" src="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Dollarphotoclub_99359996resized-300x200.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="200" /></a>\n\nMoving into a new home is always a big ordeal with the packing, hiring movers, unpacking and moving the family to a new location. Sometimes it’s easy to forget the little things, such as packing an essentials box for moving day.\n\nAn essentials box can be beneficial for each member of the family. Here are some of things that should be in your essentials box to keep your moving day moving smoothly.\n\n<strong>Water and snacks</strong>\n\nDon’t forget to eat! Packing some portable snacks and bottles of water can be a lifesaver on moving day. Granola bars, trail mix, and even dried fruit make healthy, filling snacks to keep you and your family moving. Hydration is also key on moving day. You want to stay hydrated especially after you have been moving and unpacking boxes.\n\n<strong>Important documents</strong>\n\nYou always want to know where your important or sensitive documents are throughout the whole process. This is why keeping them in an essentials box can help you keep track of their location at all times. These documents include birth certificates, passports, social security cards, etc.\n\n<strong>Toiletries</strong>\n\nYou don’t want to have to make additional stops to the drugstore during your move. Packing things like your essential toiletries, a roll of toilet paper, dish towels, and some dish soap can prove to be a big lifesaver.\n\n<strong>A change of clothes or two</strong>\n\nBring at least one pair of clean clothes for each member of the family. If the weather is less than ideal, these clothes can come in handy at the end of the day. You want to be comfortable when you’re in your new home, and clean clothes are always a good start.\n\nFor all of your residential moving needs, contact Austin Moving Forward, Austin’s premiere moving company.', 'Essentials Box: An Essential For Moving Day', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'essentials-box-an-essential-for-moving-day', '', '', '2016-01-28 18:30:17', '2016-01-28 18:30:17', '', 0, 'http://www.austinmovingforward.com/?p=1211', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1216, 2, '2016-02-13 02:45:20', '2016-02-13 02:45:20', '<a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Vantage-Points.jpg"></a>Did you know that the average move requires 60 cardboard boxes? Those 60 boxes are equivalent to more than half of a 1 ton pine tree.\n\nThese staggering numbers can have a detrimental, long-term effect on the environment which is why being environmentally conscious is crucial throughout the moving process.\n\nHere are some of the ways you can help reduce your carbon footprint during your residential move.\n\n<strong>De-clutter before the move</strong>\n\nLighten the load. Moving items that you no longer need takes unnecessary amounts of your time and your resources. The less boxes you use for your move, the better – for both you and the environment. As an added bonus, you’ll be able to use a smaller truck or make less trips during your move, reducing fuel emissions. The environment will thank you!\n\n<strong>Get creative with what you already have</strong>\n\nChances are, you have plastic totes, suitcases, or laundry baskets, right? All of these things can be substituted for cardboard moving boxes. Get creative with the storage items you already own, saving you the hassle of having to use the cardboard boxes. To take it a step further, you can even wrap your breakables with towels, t-shirts, or even newspaper. This will significantly decrease the amount of packing paper or peanuts you’ll have to use, benefitting both you and the environment.\n\n<strong>Choose an eco-friendly moving company</strong>\n\nAustin Moving Forward is committed to being an eco-friendly company and was founded with a strong consciousness towards the environment. Our founder is a busy mother of two who felt it was important that children and future generations grow up in a less toxic world. This is our company’s core belief. We use recycled boxes, wrapping paper and plastic, biodegradable packing adhesives and we offer a signature program called our Box Buy-Back Program to reduce our carbon footprint.\n\nOur Box Buy-Back Program is one of the programs that makes Austin Moving Forward unique,environmentally conscious residential mover. Here’s how it works. You leave us a deposit in the amount of the cost of the boxes. This deposit is refundable at half the cost of what you paid, so long as we get the boxes back in re-usable condition within two weeks after your delivery date. You can keep as many as you like, but you won’t get money back for the ones you keep. After you unpack the boxes they must be returned to our location during business hours, folded flat. We then re-use those boxes! Eventually, when the boxes are no longer usable, we recycle them. The Box Buy Back Program is for customers in the Austin Metro area only.\n\nIf you’re planning a residential move, keep these easy tips in mind to stay eco-friendly by reducing your carbon footprint.', 'How to Stay Eco-Friendly during Your Move', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'how-to-stay-eco-friendly-during-your-move', '', '', '2016-02-13 02:45:20', '2016-02-13 02:45:20', '', 0, 'http://www.austinmovingforward.com/?p=1216', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1255, 2, '2016-02-19 15:29:12', '2016-02-19 15:29:12', '<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1258 size-medium" src="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/1Dollarphotoclub_79751396-300x200.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="200" />\n\nMoving will always bring a lot of “new” to your life. You’ll be in a new environment, meet new people, and settle into a new place that you’ll learn to call home. The new elements can present challenges if you’re not properly prepared – especially if you’re moving to a whole new city.\n\nHere are some of the things you should consider when moving to a new city.\n\n<strong>Basic needs</strong>\n\nHousing is, of course, one of the biggest expenses you’ll face in your new location. Housing costs can range immensely even inside one city. However, housing is not the only expense. Basic needs such as utilities, groceries, transportation and healthcare have costs varying from city to city and even within the city. Make sure you consider these factors when you’re planning to move to a new city.\n\n<strong>Weather</strong>\n\nAre you a sunny weather person? Or would you prefer cold and rainy? Is your vehicle prepped for snow and rugged mountain terrain? Or would you prefer a coastline drive? The weather is a huge factor in your day to day activities and lifestyle. Keep the weather in mind before you make the big move.\n\n<strong>Schools and school districts</strong>\n\nIf you’re moving with kids, checking your new area’s school district is essential. Realtors in your new city are generally well-versed in the school districts there and can help provide you with insight into what schooling options are available and which schools might match your children’s educational needs.\n\n<strong>Other neighborhood features</strong>\n\nIt’s also key to perform a thorough search for other features in the new city such as crime rate, community events, and access to shopping, grocery stores, and gyms. If possible, try and explore the new location to get a feel for the place you could be calling home in the near future. It’s important to determine which aspects of life are most important to you and if the new city can accommodate those aspects. You want make sure your new city and new neighborhood feel like home.\n\nIf you’re looking to move to or from Austin, Austin Moving Forward is Austin’s premier residential moving company. We strive to make the move to a new city as smooth and seamless as possible.<a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/get-a-quote/"> Contact us today for a free quote!</a>\n\n&nbsp;', 'Things to You Need to Consider When Moving to a New City', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'things-to-you-need-to-consider-when-moving-to-a-new-city', '', '', '2016-02-19 15:29:12', '2016-02-19 15:29:12', '', 0, 'http://www.austinmovingforward.com/?p=1255', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1261, 2, '2016-02-29 16:03:31', '2016-02-29 16:03:31', '<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1262 size-medium" src="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Dollarphotoclub_86905924-300x200.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="200" />\n\nMoving for the first time? Then it is time to plan your move in terms of packing, loading and unloading of all your things. Whether you are interested in hiring a professional moving company for your residential move or wanted to go for DIY moving make sure that you will plan and organize all the required things at least a month before your actual moving date. This will help you pack your things efficiently as well as help you decide if DIY moving is the right option for your residential move.\n\nIf you’re trying to decide whether DIY moving is right for you, you’ll need to first assess your budget like how much you can afford on professional moving company? Then it is necessary that you make an efficient comparison on DIY moving and professional moving. Accordingly, you will choose the best option without spending a fortune on residential moves.\n\n<strong>Pros and Cons of DIY Moving</strong>\n\n<em>Advantages</em>\n<ul>\n	<li>It will save you good amount of money.</li>\n	<li>Your friends and family can help.</li>\n	<li>You will achieve a sense of complete satisfaction that you have done all the moving by yourself.</li>\n</ul>\n<em>Disadvantages</em>\n<ul>\n	<li>If not properly planned and organized, then it can cost you a fortune.</li>\n	<li>Depending upon the quantity of stuff, your DIY moving project can waste your hours which is not quite a rational approach.</li>\n	<li>Additionally, on moving yourself you need to do the heavy lifting by yourself that can cause you physical stress or even injury.</li>\n</ul>\nIf you feel that the cons outweigh the pros of DIY moving, contact Austin Moving Forward today for a<a href="http://www.austinmovingforward.com/dont-forget-to-spring-forward/" target="_blank"> free moving quote.</a>\n\n&nbsp;', 'Pros and Cons of DIY Residential Moves', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'pros-and-cons-of-diy-residential-moves', '', '', '2016-02-29 16:03:31', '2016-02-29 16:03:31', '', 0, 'http://www.austinmovingforward.com/?p=1261', 0, 'post', '', 0);
